The '''[[Republican Party (United States)|Republican Party]]''', also commonly called the '''GOP''' (abbreviation for '''Grand Old Party'''), is one of the [[Two-party system|two]] [[Major party|major]] contemporary [[political parties in the United States]], the other being the [[Democratic Party (United States)|Democratic Party]]. Founded by anti-slavery activists in 1854, it dominated politics nationally for most of the period from 1860 to 1932. There have been 19 Republican presidents, the first being [[Abraham Lincoln]], serving from 1861 to 1865, and the most recent being [[Donald Trump]].

This is a list of the official state and territorial party organizations of the [[Republican Party (United States)|Republican Party]].

